data.title: TerraMaster to release TOS 7 NAS operating system after 2 years of development, with chance to win new USB4 NVMe SSD drive enclosure D1 SSD Plus.

data.title: AAPL releases new book, Core Versus Chore, to tackle healthcare burnout, inefficiency using human-centered design.
data.description: Today, in Washington on October 31, 2025, the American Association for Physician Leadership (AAPL) revealed the launch of their latest publication, titled Core Versus Chore: Using Human-Centered Design to Address Burnout and Inefficiencies in Healthcare. The book is authored by a distinguished physician leader within the healthcare industry and aims to provide insights on tackling burnout and inefficiencies.

data.title: Palantir co-founder warns that AI giants need more funding every 3-6 months but are afraid to scare investors. Investment underestimation in the AI space.
data.description: Joe Lonsdale, co-founder of Palantir Technologies Inc. (NASDAQ: PLTR), recently expressed concerns that industry leaders in artificial intelligence (AI) are underestimating the resources needed to meet their ambitious goals. Lonsdale, who is also the founder of venture firm 8VC, warned of a continuous cycle every 3-6 months where executives are constantly seeking more capital and energy to drive their initiatives forward. Speaking on CNBC's "Squawk Box," he highlighted that AI companies may be downplaying their true needs out of fear of alarming investors. Lonsdale emphasized the importance of acknowledging the significant investment required in the AI space, indicating that current estimations may fall short of the actual amount needed. This insight reflects a potentially greater demand for resources in the AI industry than previously anticipated.

data.title: Xole AI introduces AI-powered platform for creating hyper-realistic spooky videos and images for Halloween in seconds, no design skills needed.
data.description: An innovative platform has been introduced that allows people to generate incredibly lifelike spooky videos and images instantly, without the need for any design expertise. This advancement reflects the growing trend of leveraging technology for creative pursuits, making it accessible to a broader audience.

data.title: 73% of legal clients find attorneys online, but highly qualified lawyers suffer visibility issues, losing millions in business.
data.description: A recent study conducted in New York reported a significant disparity in how legal clients are being acquired. According to the research, a staggering 73% of legal clients are now discovering their lawyers through online platforms. However, despite this trend, a large number of highly skilled attorneys are not being prominently featured in these searches. This oversight is causing them to lose out on potential business opportunities to lesser experienced competitors.

data.title: Yonsei University creates high-voltage solid-state batteries with groundbreaking fluoride-based electrolyte, surpassing voltage limits.
data.description: A revolutionary solid electrolyte based on fluoride has been created by researchers in Seoul, South Korea, marking a significant breakthrough in battery technology. The electrolyte has surpassed traditional voltage limits, paving the way for enhanced performance in next-generation batteries. The development comes from Yonsei University and was announced on October 31, 2025. This innovation is set to transform the battery landscape with its advanced capabilities and has the potential to significantly impact various industries.

data.description: On October 31, 2025, in Los Angeles, BVP (Big Vision Pictures) revealed plans for the production of two new feature films by Laurice E. Molinari. This next-generation film and television studio is known for combining Hollywood storytelling with Web3 innovation. data.title: Jimmy's Jazz & Blues Club in Portsmouth, NH will host a month of performances in November including Grammy-winning artists and local talents.
data.description: In Portsmouth, New Hampshire, Jimmy's Jazz & Blues Club is gearing up for an exciting November lineup of performances as temperatures cool down. Throughout the month, the club will host a variety of acts including Grammy-winning artists, soulful singers, acclaimed jazz groups, and beloved local talents. The diverse schedule promises something for everyone, with each night offering unique and unforgettable entertainment. This month-long event is set to showcase the talents of a range of musicians, making it a must-visit destination for music lovers.
